<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9796> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9796" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Additions and Corrections. See now G. Downey, \"The Occupation of Syria by the Romans,\" TAPhA 72 (1951) 149-163. Since recruitment of soldiers for the amry of Marcius Rex was already in progress in Cisalpine Gaul in 68 it is possible that he arrived in his province somewhat earlier than Downey supposes (p 152). See Suet. Iul. 8; and 69, Quaestors, on Caesar. See also p 154, 66 BC, Promagistrates, on Q. Marcus Rex." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8767> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8767" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 749" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4869> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4869" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (see 67-64, Promagistrates). Still waiting outside Rome for permission to celebrate his triumph, he was sent to check the forces of Catiline's Lieutenant Manlius in Etruria at Faesulae (Sall. Cat. 30.3; 33.1-34.1). There is no mention of his triumph, and he died before May 15, 61 (Cic. Att. 1.16.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4833> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4833" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His triumph was still obstructed. See 67-63, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4797> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4797" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 67-62, Promagistrates. His demand for a triumph continued to be obstructed." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4770> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4770" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia (see 67, Promagistrates). Superseded by Pompey under the Manilian law (Dio 36.42-43, cf. 48.2). He was saluted as Imperator and demanded a triumph (Sall. Cat. 30.3-4; 33.1; see 63, and 62, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4705> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4705" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia with three legions (Sall. Hist. 5.13-14 M; Dio 36.15.1, and 17.2; cf. CIL 12.2.747). Malalas notes his presence in Antioch in 67 or 66 (225, lines 7-11, ed. Bonn.; cf. Diod. 40.1a-b, in FHG 2.xxiv-xxvi; Dio 36.17.2-3; Jerome Chr. ad ann. 68, p. 153 Helm; see G. Downey, CPh 32 [1937] 144-151)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4641> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4641" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.905, 956; Dio 36.4.1; Chr. 354 (Metello et Vatia); Fast. Hyd. (Marcio Rege et Metello), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Marcius, CIL 12.2.747, and perhaps 660 (but see 118, Consuls). See Degrassi 131, 488f. Metellus died early in the year (Dio 36.4.1). Cilicia was withdrawn from the command of Lucullus and assigned to Marcius (Dio 36.2.2; cf. Suet. Iul. 8; see 67, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4535> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4535" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 The latest date possible under the Cornelian law." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10258> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10258" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph? ex Cilicia. outside city in late 63 awaiting permission to triumph. Dispatched to fight Catilinarian forces in Italy. Unknown if permission was ever granted. Not listed in Itgenshorst or Rich." .
